The paper deals with the concept of mutual information, which is a fundamental concept in information theory (cs.IT). It also discusses the decomposition of mutual information into its components, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.DS). The paper proposes new postulates for the decomposition of mutual information, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information science (cs.SI).
